Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @sweet potatoes{2} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{1%tbsp}, sprinkle
over the @Mexican style spice mix{1%sachet}, season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%mins}. Turn
halfway through.

When the wedges have roasted for ~{5%mins}, pop the @Cumberland sausages{8}
on the #tray{} alongside.

Return to the oven and bake for the remaining time, until golden brown and
cooked through. Turn halfway through.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. The sausages
> are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, trim the @baby gem lettuce{1}, separate the leaves, then tear into
bite-sized pieces.

Cut the @lime{1} into wedges.

== Dressing ==

In a #medium bowl{}, combine a good squeeze of lime juice from a lime wedge,
@honey{1%tbsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing (see pantry for both).
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Set your dressing aside.

== Assembly ==

When everything's cooked, add the baby gem to the dressing. Toss to coat.

Remove the sausage tray from the oven. Drizzle the @red pepper chilli jelly{25%g}
over the sausages and turn to evenly glaze.

Share the sausages between your plates. Spoon over any remaining glaze from the
tray.

Serve the sweet potato wedges, salad and remaining lime wedges alongside.

Sprinkle the @salted peanuts{25%g} over the salad. Finish with a dollop of
@mayonnaise{32%g} for dipping.

Enjoy!